   were satisfied because itâ€™s still an ad posted and showing us to their
   followers,â€ said the owner, who nonetheless asked to remain anonymous
   to prevent other would-be influencers from trying to dine for free.

   Advertisers may not mind, but human influencers are wary of automating
   their profession. â€œTo be honest, seeing someone create such a large
   following through automation and AI is pretty discouraging for me, and
   for anyone else who has put blood, sweat, and tears into building their
   online brands,â€ Skyler Bouchard (@diningwithskyler), a New York
   Cityâ€“based food Instagrammer with 175,000 followers, told BuzzFeed
